Whereas, on July 16, 2008, the District of Columbia
			 enacted the Firearms Control Emergency Amendment Act of 2008 (D.C. Act 17–422;
			 55 DCR 8237), which places onerous restrictions on the ability of law-abiding
			 citizens from possessing firearms, thus violating the spirit by which the
			 Supreme Court of the United States ruled in District of Columbia v. Heller;
			 and
